    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 4. Discretization error achieves Gradation 3 against a requirement of 2, providing additional margin. The UQ campaign (200 LHS samples, 6 parameters) confirms that worst-case operating point identification is robust to input uncertainty, with rotational speed and gap clearance identified as dominant sensitivity drivers. The relative hemolysis index criterion (RH < 1) is satisfied at all five validation operating points with a mean absolute relative error of 8.3 %. The credibility assessment team unanimously accepts the model as fit for the stated COU at the Medium assurance level.",
